---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout>
  <div class="bookmarks">
    <h1>bookmarked</h1>
    <p>
      Welcome to my curated collection of internet curiosities – a smattering of websites, 
      videos, and products that are either surprisingly useful or gloriously trivial. 
      Consider it a running commentary on the absurdity of our digital age.
    </p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="https://thisissand.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          This is Sand
        </a> – a strangely relaxing digital sandbox where you can create mesmerizing sand art.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.zooniverse.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Zooniverse
        </a> – help real scientists by classifying galaxies, wildlife, and ancient manuscripts.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.ocearch.org/tracker/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Ocearch Shark Tracker
        </a> – track tagged sharks, turtles, and whales in real time.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.themarginalian.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          The Marginalian
        </a> – previously Brain Pickings; essays and insights from philosophy, literature, and art.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://neal.fun/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Neal.fun
        </a> – a playground of weird interactive experiments.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://zoomquilt.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Zoom Quilt
        </a> – mind-bending, infinitely zooming piece of digital artwork.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://radio.garden/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Radio Garden
        </a> – listen to live radio stations from anywhere in the world by spinning a globe.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://pudding.cool/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          The Pudding
        </a> – data-driven essays on pop culture, music, and internet phenomena.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://waitbutwhy.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Wait But Why
        </a> – deep-dive, thought-provoking articles on everything from AI to procrastination.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.koalastothemax.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Koalas to the Max
        </a> – huge dots break into smaller dots infinitely as you move your mouse.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://stars.chromeexperiments.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Stars.chromeexperiments
        </a> – a 3D map of the entire universe you can fly through.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.cameronsworld.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Cameron's World
        </a> – a chaotic but nostalgic collage of old GeoCities pages.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="http://www.staggeringbeauty.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Staggering Beauty
        </a> – wiggle a worm with your mouse and prepare for a surprise.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
